---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout sideBarActiveItemID="about">
  <div class="pb-12 mt-5">
    <div class="text-xl py-1">Hello, and welcome!</div>
    <div class="text-5xl font-bold">I'm Jared Kominsky</div>
    <div class="text-3xl py-3 font-bold">
      DevOps & Site Reliability Engineer
    </div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <p class="text-lg">
        I design, build, and maintain cloud-native systems that are scalable, resilient, and
        efficient. My work centers on bridging Site Reliability Engineering principles with
        DevOps practices to deliver infrastructure that enables rapid development without
        compromising reliability.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div>
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">How I Work</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-lg space-y-2">
        <li>
          I analyze usage data before capacity decisions—at Groups360, I reviewed six months of CPU and memory metrics before right-sizing, reducing infrastructure costs by 40%.
        </li>
        <li>
          I validate scaling under load before production—at Groups360, I ran k6 load tests to confirm HPA policies matched real traffic patterns.
        </li>
        <li>
          I design monitoring for signal quality, not volume—at Built Technologies, I built alerting for 40+ microservices focused on actionable signals, reducing incident response time by 75%.
        </li>
        <li>
          I enforce standards through automation—at Groups360, I used Terraform to manage 200+ repositories with consistent branch protection and CI requirements.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Professional Journey</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <p class="text-lg">
        At Groups360, I reduced infrastructure costs by 40%, cut observability spend by 35%, and migrated EKS to Terraform IaC. I drove Argo CD GitOps adoption and automated 200+ repository configurations with Terraform.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg mt-4">
        At Built Technologies, I owned monitoring for 40+ microservices, reducing incident response time by 75%, and built test automation that cut CI/CD cycle time by 75%.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">What I'm Building</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <p class="text-lg">
        I recently built and operate <a href="/projects/unifyops" class="link link-primary font-semibold">UnifyOps</a>, an internal developer platform I designed and run end-to-end. It deploys multi-service systems safely using GitOps, Kubernetes, and strict runtime isolation.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg mt-4">
        Other active projects:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-3 text-lg space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Job Scanner</strong> — An LLM-powered automation pipeline using GPT-4 for
          intelligent job screening, fit scoring, and automated outreach generation
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Auth Platform</strong> — A production-ready microservices authentication
          system with JWT flows, deployed via Helm charts to self-hosted Harbor registry
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Stack Templates</strong> — Reusable microservice scaffolding implementing
          three-tier architecture patterns with pre-configured CI/CD
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-lg mt-4">
        All projects are deployed to my home lab infrastructure — bare-metal Kubernetes
        running on personal servers with Harbor registry, demonstrating end-to-end DevOps
        practices from code to production.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Core Expertise</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-lg">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Infrastructure & Orchestration</p>
          <p class="text-base">Kubernetes, EKS, Terraform, Helm, Argo CD</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Cloud & Architecture</p>
          <p class="text-base">AWS, multi-AZ, high availability, GitOps</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Observability</p>
          <p class="text-base">Datadog, APM, distributed tracing, SLIs/SLOs</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Automation</p>
          <p class="text-base">GitHub Actions, CI/CD, Python, Bash</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Awards & Recognition</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <p class="text-lg">
        I earned the <strong>Built Onward Award</strong> at Built Technologies, given to less than 10%
        of team members for sustained impact and ownership. At Belmont University,
        I received the <strong>Stephen Campbell Math & Computer Science Award</strong> (one
        recipient per year) and made the Dean's List consistently.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Scale I've Supported</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold">40+</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Microservices monitored</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold">200+</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Repositories managed</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold">3</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Environments (dev/staging/prod)</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold">30+</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Monitors and alerts</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">What I'm Looking For</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-lg space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Role type:</strong> Senior SRE, Platform Engineer, or DevOps Engineer with infrastructure ownership
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Problem space:</strong> Kubernetes platforms, observability, cost optimization, or internal developer tooling
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ownership scope:</strong> Full ownership of production infrastructure, not just support or consulting
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Let's Connect</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <p class="text-lg">
        I'm always eager to connect with teams building reliable, scalable infrastructure.
        Whether you're looking for someone to own your Kubernetes platform, optimize your
        observability stack, or implement GitOps workflows — let's talk.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8">
      <a
        class="btn"
        href="https://linkedin.com/in/jared-kominsky"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Connect on LinkedIn
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/KominskyOrg"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="btn btn-outline ml-5"
      >
        Visit My GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-2">Outside of Work</div>
    <div class="py-2">
      <p class="text-lg">
        I enjoy hydroponic gardening, tennis, traveling, and exploring Nashville's food scene.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
